HOW TO INITRAMFS
================

0. Updating initramfs


  sudo mkinitcpio -P
  sudo grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg

1. Enable fallback


  sudo nvim /etc/mkinitcpio.d/linux-lts.preset

  comment PRESETS=('default')
  uncomment #PRESETS=('default', 'fallback')

2. Disable splash


  sudo nvim /etc/mkinitcpio.d/linux-lts.preset

  comment default_options="--splash /usr/share/systemd/bootctl/splash-arch.bmp"

3. Using systemd as init


  sudo nvim /etc/mkinitcpio.d/linux-lts.preset

  add "-A systemd,sd-vconsole -S base,udev,keymap,consolefont" into default_options

4. Minimal initramfs


  sudo nvim /etc/mkinitcpio.d/linux-lts.preset

  add "-S keyboard,consolefont,fsck,filesystems" into default_options
